    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1928"/>, p. 326, n. <citedRange>3-4</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.86</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>111, 116</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>38.1894</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>018000</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, pp. <citedRange>325-326</citedRange>, number 66 b (text)s</bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#pernier1935"/>, p. <citedRange>70</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-66108"><name nymRef="#Φίλων">Φίλων</name> <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62907"><name nymRef="#Αννικερις" type="patronymic">Αννικεριος</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων">Ἀπόλλωνι</name></persName> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέθηκε</w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Philôn fils d'Annikeris a consacré à Apollon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Philon son of Annikeris dedicated to Apollo.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Philon figlio di Annikeris ha dedicato ad Apollo.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>C. Dobias-Lalou thought that because of the bad light and of growing trees, she was never able to see those two sister inscriptions, whereas the more developed dedication <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr017900</ref>
                is much more conspicuous. E. Rosamilia neither could find it. If its support is really preserved, the inscription may have disappeared because of natural decay.</p>
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl> reminds that, as <bibl><ptr target="#stucchi1975"/>, p. <citedRange>59</citedRange></bibl> put it, this inscription might 
                refer only to the dedication of metal objects which were inserted into the marble cornices and not to the marble covering of the whole altar, to which <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr017900</ref> surely refers.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
